# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js e-commerce application using modern tools and practices. Here's the key directory structure:

## Core Directories
- [app/](mdc:app) - Contains the Next.js application routes and pages
- [components/](mdc:components) - Reusable React components
- [actions/](mdc:actions) - Server actions and API endpoints
- [lib/](mdc:lib) - Utility functions and shared libraries
- [prisma/](mdc:prisma) - Database schema and migrations
- [public/](mdc:public) - Static assets

## Key Configuration Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts
- [next.config.mjs](mdc:next.config.mjs) - Next.js configuration
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - UI components configuration
- [middleware.js](mdc:middleware.js) - Next.js middleware for authentication and routing
- [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css) - Global styles and Tailwind configuration

